00:01:02.910 --> 00:01:05.930
A specific work that was very challenging?

00:01:05.930 --> 00:01:12.350
There were several, including Elijah that
we're in right now in the middle of; challenging

00:01:12.350 --> 00:01:16.460
in a different way, challenging because Elijah
just has a whole lot of music for the chorus.

00:01:16.460 --> 00:01:18.460
We have to tell a story.

00:01:18.460 --> 00:01:22.330
So it's not enough to know the notes and the
rhythms and the words; but we have to be able

00:01:22.330 --> 00:01:25.750
to communicate that in a way that makes it
compelling.

00:01:25.750 --> 00:01:27.280
Because it is a story.

00:01:27.280 --> 00:01:36.850
It is all of these stories around Elijah's
life and his work, and so we are there, the

00:01:36.850 --> 00:01:41.300
music has to come alive as if we were actually
there and in the course of the action.

00:01:41.300 --> 00:01:43.060
So, that's our challenge.

00:01:43.060 --> 00:01:46.670
The Choral Union tends to always rise to the
occasion.

