00:02:02.920 --> 00:02:05.870
We've grown in numbers, the group has gotten
a lot larger.

00:02:05.870 --> 00:02:14.670
I would say we've grown in selectivity, how
we can make choices from those who audition.

00:02:14.670 --> 00:02:20.409
We have grown in balance, the balance is a
little better between soprano, alto, tenor,

00:02:20.409 --> 00:02:23.990
and bass, than it was when I started.

00:02:23.990 --> 00:02:27.730
I didn't start things, the Choral Union had
been around a long time before me, it'll be

00:02:27.730 --> 00:02:30.520
around a long time after me.

00:02:30.520 --> 00:02:36.100
If there's something that I could say to the
Choral Union as I leave them, and that sounds

00:02:36.100 --> 00:02:42.819
awfully final because we still have a whole
lot of work to do.... would just be to let

00:02:42.819 --> 00:02:49.460
them know how grateful I am to them for their
love, for their support, for their dedication,

00:02:49.460 --> 00:02:56.030
for how many people drive so far and give
up Monday evenings so often and weeks as we

00:02:56.030 --> 00:02:57.030
go into Detroit.

00:02:57.030 --> 00:02:59.220
It's wonderful, I'm grateful for that.

00:02:59.220 --> 00:03:03.490
It has been an honor to stand on the podium
in front of you every week, and to lead you

00:03:03.490 --> 00:03:08.500
in Messiahs and to prepare you for other orchestras
and conductors; it's been a great privilege,

00:03:08.500 --> 00:03:15.610
a privilege that I will treasure for the rest
of my life.

00:03:15.610 --> 00:03:22.230
So my motivation has been because I love that
repertoire; it's the repertoire that I have

00:03:22.230 --> 00:03:29.599
spent my life studying and the opportunity
to do it consistently, to develop a chorus

00:03:29.599 --> 00:03:47.060
who can do it with skill has been a real motivation.

